<title>THAILAND: Thai bourse warns speculators on finance mergers.</title>
<headline>Thai bourse warns speculators on finance mergers.</headline>
<dateline>BANGKOK 1997-06-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Stock Exchange of Thailand on Wednesday urged investors to exercise caution in speculating on finance company mergers after cabinet measures to encourage cash-strapped firms to consolidate through corporate alliances.</p>
<p>The bourse said investors should closely monitor any possible mergers and base their investment decisions only on official announcements by listed firms.</p>
<p>The Thai cabinet on Tuesday approved four executive decrees to encourage cash-strapped finance firms to merge and outline measures to bail out finance and property firms hit by a prolonged liquidity crunch and business slump.</p>
<p>-- Bangkok newsroom (662) 652-0642</p>
